# Security Policy — {{ project_name }}

## Supported Versions

| Version | Supported |
|---------|-----------|
| 0.x.x   | ✅ Yes    |

## Reporting a Vulnerability

Please report security vulnerabilities by emailing the maintainers directly.
Do NOT create a public GitHub issue for security vulnerabilities.

## Security Controls

Implemented by the Calango Framework:

- JWT RS256 authentication (when identity plugin active)
- Automatic security headers (X-Content-Type-Options, HSTS, X-Frame-Options)
- Global exception handler — never exposes stack traces in production
- CORS closed by default — origins must be explicitly configured
- Rate limiting on authentication endpoints
- Argon2 password hashing (when identity plugin active)

## Threat Model

### Critical assets
- [ ] User credentials and tokens
- [ ] Personal data (PII)
- [ ] Financial data (if applicable)

### Attack surface
- [ ] Public endpoints (no authentication required)
- [ ] Authenticated endpoints
- [ ] Incoming webhooks from external services
- [ ] Background jobs with privileged access
